1) Install Flutter and Android tooling (Android Studio + SDK + accept licenses).

2) In this folder, generate the Android/iOS wrapper projects (keeps your lib/ + pubspec):
   flutter create .

3) Fetch packages:
   flutter pub get

4) Debug on a device/emulator:
   flutter run

5) Release APK:
   flutter build apk

Notes:
- The "Ask AI" tab needs network permission (default in Flutter templates) and a key/base URL in Settings.
- Full patch 4.7 wiki data is not bundled: use Settings -> Import catalog JSON (offline file you create or export legally).

Optional — build in the cloud (no local Flutter):
- Treat this folder (where pubspec.yaml is) as the Git repo root.
- Push to GitHub. Open Actions → "Build Android APK" → run workflow → download the "app-release-apk" artifact (ZIP contains the APK).
